Description:
The LocationIQ Direction Service Curl Sample Code in beta stage demonstrates how to access the API and provides a mapping guide based on work by the OSRM Project. OSRM is a C++ routing engine for the shortest paths in road networks.
To learn more, visit <a href="http://project-osrm.org/">Open Source Routing Machine.

The LocationIQ Static Maps JavaScript Sample Code demonstrates how to access the API to implement static maps in JPG or PNG format. When developers make a request, they can place markers or draw paths at locations on the map and embed a static map image within a tag's src attribute.

The LocationIQ Static Maps PHP Sample Code demonstrates how to access the API to implement static maps in JPG or PNG format. The Static Maps API returns an image in response to an HTTP request. For each request, developers can specify the map's location, size of the image, zoom level, and type of map.
The LocationIQ Static Maps PHP Sample Code demonstrates how to access the API to implement static maps with key, center, zoom, scale, size, format, map type, markers, and path as query parameters.
The LocationIQ Static Maps Curl Sample Code demonstrates how to access the API and provides an endpoint in v2 that allows developers to make requests. Available usage and query parameters.

The Bank of Hodlers Cryptocurrency Wallet JavaScript Sample Code demonstrates how to interact with the Wallet API. Bank of Hodlers provides JavaScript bindings with relevant sample codes at <a href="http://docs.bankofhodlers.com/#authentication">http://docs.bankofhodlers.com/#authentication

The LocationIQ Autocomplete Curl Sample Code demonstrates how to predict places in response to an HTTP request. The service can be used to return places such as businesses, addresses, and points of interest.
The LocationIQ Points of Interest JavaScript Sample Code demonstrates how to access the API with a private token, add restaurant radius as a tag, use a GET verb, and JSON format.

The LocationIQ Points of Interest Python Sample Code demonstrates how to make requests to the API, use a private token as a key, and include latitude, longitude, a location tag (restaurant), radius, and format (JSON).
The LocationIQ Points of Interest PHP Sample Code demonstrates how to access the API with a private token. The example shows how developers can access restaurant radius in JSON formats.
The LocationIQ Points of Interest Curl Sample Code demonstrates how to make GET requests to the API, use a private token, and receive a response to implement POI in location services.
The LocationIQ Maps JavaScript Sample Code demonstrates how to access unwired maps that provide worldwide street and satellite maps. Developers can generate access tokens on a user dashboard.
The LocationIQ Maps Python Sample Code demonstrates how to implement map tile URLs, desktop maps with Mapbox GL, desktop maps with Leaflet, and use mobile SDKs.

The LocationIQ Maps PHP Sample Code demonstrates how to access the API to implement mapping into location services. It is recommended that developers use Mapbox's open-source GL javascript library for web projects and iOS and Android SDKs for mobile projects.
The LocationIQ Maps Curl Sample Code demonstrates how to access Unwired Maps that provide world-wide street and satellite maps.

The City of Calgary Public Trees Power Shell Sample Code demonstrates how to access the API with a token, how to set a header to accept JSON, and how to invoke a REST method via URI.

The City of Calgary Public Trees jQuery Sample Code demonstrates how to fetch and parse JSON from an API endpoint. Developers can use GET requests to access the API.

This Go Sample Code demonstrates how to enable service invocations. This is specific to device to device networks.
This Go Sample Code demonstrates how to encode handler responses. The test application sends an OK to the topic to avoid redelivering when the binding output has been accepted.

This Go Sample Code demonstrates how to encode handler responses. The test application sends an OK to the topic to avoid redelivering when the binding input has been accepted.

The Tracktry List Carriers PHP Sample Code demonstrates how to list all carriers by giving the command new Tracktry to get a carrier list.
The Tracktry Detect Carrier by Code PHP Sample Code demonstrates how to detect a carrier with a tracking number and the command new Tracktry.

The ShipEngine Rate Estimates Curl Sample Code demonstrates how to provide good estimate rates with postal code to, postal code from, weight, and dimensions.

The ShipEngine Shipping Size and Weight Curl Sample Code demonstrates how to include weight (unit and value) and dimensions (unit, length, width, and height). For ShipEngine, accuracy is key.

The ShipEngine Validate Address Curl Sample Code demonstrates how to validate an address. Address validation ensures accurate addresses and can lead to reduced shipping costs by preventing address correction surcharges.

The ShipEngine Parse Address Curl Sample Code demonstrates how to parse an address with over 90% accuracy. When users receive an order via email, they can send the text of the email to ShipEngine and it will automatically extract the customer's address.

This Swift Sample Code includes a template app with the necessary components to implement rewards systems. The test application packages several modules including brand, feed, referral, user, social media friend, and location.

The Mendix First Script Node.js Sample Code demonstrates how to write a script that will use the Mendix Platform SDK. The script creates a new app, adds a new entity to the domain model, and commits the changes to the Team Server.
The Mendix Development Environment Node.js Sample Code demonstrates how to set up development tools and create an SDK script to bootstrap a new Mendix app.
The Mendix Deploy .NET Sample Code demonstrates how to set up an environment, write an app name, and access with username and an API Key.

The Geocodio Accuracy Score PHP Sample Code demonstrates how to display accurate score with forward geocoding and reverse geocoding. Values cover rooftop, nearest street, and nearest place.
